casebody.data:
Carlos CASANOVA, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Jorge Luis MORALES, Defendant-Appellee. No. 07-14145

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Jan. 10, 2008. Jamie H. Zidell, J.H. Zidell, P.A., Miami Beach, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellant. Before ANDERSON, BARRETT and HULL, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

We find no error in the District Court’s determination that Carlos Casanova has failed to establish coverage under the Fair Labor Standards Act, 29 U.S.C. §§ 201-216, and thus, the Summary Judgment in favor of Jorge Luis Morales is

AFFIRMED.
